      "writtenOn": "2019-07-09T06:57:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I tested in Adreno630, its GLSL version is k320es_GrGLSLGeneration. So\nctxInfo.glslGeneration() \u003c GrGLSLGeneration::k330_GrGLSLGeneration doesn\u0027t\ndisable this Extension.\n\nwhen \u0027use_es2_for_oopr\u0027 flag is enabled in Chromium, Skia uses GL ES 2.0,\nbut the GLSL version is not changed. Do we need to set GLSL ES version to k110_GrGLSLGeneration? I try this in GrGLContext::Make(...) method without\ndisable framebuffer fetch, and it works.\n\nSo there may be two options right now:\n1. current patch, it will only affect Adreno6xx devices;\n    May need to be revised.\n2. set GLSL ES version to k110_GrGLSLGeneration;\n    It could be a better solution, but it will affect more GPUs and need more testing.\n    This can be modified in Chromium code:\n    https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/ui/gl/init/create_gr_gl_interface.cc?type\u003dcs\u0026g\u003d0\u0026l\u003d135",
